<subSubSection pageNumber="291" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageNumber="291">
Munro (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="291">J. Proc. Linn. Soc., Bot.</emphasis>
6: 53. 1862) noted the existence of two species associated with this name in LINN, and Hitchcock (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="291">Contr. U. S. Natl. Herb.</emphasis>
12: 126. 1908) provided an extensive discussion. However, Henrard (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="291">Blumea</emphasis>
3: 454. 1940) clearly accepted the sheet now numbered as 1211.27 (LINN) as the type, though the material it bears is a mixed collection. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Henrard’s">Henrard's</normalizedToken>
type choice was therefore restricted by Cope to the lower, central specimen, in accordance with Art. 9.15.
</paragraph>
